Even if an experimental vaccine seems so far to be able to reduce the mortality rate of Ebola, no remedy has yet been sufficiently effective to treat the existing infection.
Even though the administration of a cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, had initially shown promising signs in the field, formal studies have shown that its ability to limit deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, ZMapp was used as a control, which means that the scientists used it as a reference and compared the three other treatments to it.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter of the U.S. Olympic Committee and accepts the absolute need of the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the statement of the USOC (United States Olympic Committee) that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, as well as their sport, could be better served. This can be done by going forward and proceeding rather to significant changes within our organization, rather than revocation of accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on the way in which the abuse described so courageously by the survivors of Larry Nassar was able to go unnoticed for so long and adopts all necessary and appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics, as well as other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can continue to pursue their dreams in a safe, positive and responsible environment.
Tout au long des années 1960, Brzezinski a travaillé pour John F. Kennedy en tant que conseiller, puis pour l'administration de Lyndon B. Johnson.
During the 1976 elections, he advised Carter on foreign policy, then served as National Security Advisor (NSA) from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
During his time at the NSA, he helped Carter resolve diplomatic issues such as the Camp David Accords in 1978, the normalization of relations between the United States and China in the late 1970s, the Iranian Revolution and its consequences, such as the hostage crisis in Iran in 1979, and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan in 1979.
