The 802.11n standard works on both the 2.4 GHz and 5.0 GHz frequencies.
This will authorize retro-compatibility with 802.11a, b and g iterations, provided that the station has two radios.
The speeds of the Wi-Fi 802.11n standard are significantly faster than those of its predecessors, with a theoretical maximum speed of 600 Mbit/s.
